    <static seed="8" source="Contrib/CCCS/AlgebraicLiteracy/Equations_of_Lines/Slope_1.pg">
      <statement><p>Find the slope of the line that passes through the following points</p>
<p><m>(8,-8)</m>  and  <m>(-3,10)</m>.</p>
<p>Write your answer as an integer or fraction.</p>
<p><fillin characters="4" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>-{\frac{18}{11}}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>Slope can be computed by taking the change in y divided by the change in x:</p>
<p><m>m = \frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}</m></p>
<p>I am going to let <m>x_1 = 8</m>, <m>y_1 = -8</m>, <m>x_2 = -3</m>, and <m>y_2 = 10</m>.  Plugging those numbers in my slope formula, I get:</p>
<p><m>m = \frac{10  + 8}{-3 - 8}</m></p>
<p><m>m = \frac{18}{-11}</m></p>
<p><m>m = {-{\frac{18}{11}}}</m></p>
<p><em>Note: I might have reduced my answer.</em></p>
</solution>
