      <statement><p>Fill in the blanks:</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/> is <m>94\%</m> of <m>130</m>?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>369.6</m> is <fillin characters="6" name="AnSwEr0002"/> <m>\%</m> of <m>480</m>?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>6545</m> is  <m>85\%</m> of <fillin characters="6" name="AnSwEr0003"/>?</p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>122.2</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>77</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>7700</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>This translation from English to math may help you remember the percentage formula.</p>
<p><m>2 \text{ is } 50\% \text{ of } 4 \iff 2 = 0.5 \cdot 4</m></p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p>What is <m>94\%</m> of <m>130</m>?</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \begin{aligned}
      x \amp = 0.94 \cdot 130\\
        \amp = {122.2} 
      \end{aligned}}</m></p>
<p>So <m>{122.2}</m> is <m>94\%</m> of <m>130</m>.</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to place a horizontal rule here. -->
</li>
<li>
<p><m>369.6</m> is what <m>\%</m> of <m>480</m>?</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
  369.6 \amp =\frac{x}{100} \cdot 480 \\
  100(369.6) \amp =100\cdot\frac{x}{100} \cdot 480 \\
  36960 \amp =x \cdot 480 \\
  \frac{36960}{480} \amp = \frac{x \cdot 480}{480} \\
  {77} \amp = x\\
  x \amp ={77}
\end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>So <m>369.6</m> is <m>{77}\%</m> of <m>480</m>.</p>
<!-- PTX:WARNING: PGML wanted to place a horizontal rule here. -->
</li>
<li>
<p><m>6545</m> is  <m>85\%</m> of what?</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
  6545 \amp = 0.85 \cdot x \\
  \frac{6545}{0.85} \amp = \frac{0.85 \cdot x}{0.85} \\
  {7700} \amp = x\\
  x \amp  = {7700}
\end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>So <m>6545</m> is <m>85\%</m> of <m>{7700}</m>.</p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</solution>
