      <statement><p>Baseball batting averages are somewhat similar to percentages except that they
are usually rounded to three decimal places and include the decimal point.  That is, if a player got 3 hits in 10 at bats then she had a hit <m>\frac {3}{10} = .300</m> of the times she was at bat. Her batting average is listed as .300 in the newspapers.</p>
<p>a) If Fred got 15 hits in 50 times at bat, his batting average is <fillin characters="3" name="AnSwEr0001"/>.</p>
<p>b) If Mary got 139 hits in 461 times at bat, her batting average is <fillin characters="3" name="AnSwEr0002"/>.</p>
<p>If Mary got 139 hits in 461 times at bat, then she got</p>
<p>hits <fillin characters="3" name="AnSwEr0003"/>% of the times she was at bat.</p>
<p>Answer should be correct to 1 decimal place.</p>
<p>Jack's batting average is 0.277.  He was at bat 148 times.  That means he
got <fillin characters="3" name="AnSwEr0004"/> hits.</p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>0.3</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>0.301518</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>30.2</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>41</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>SOLUTIONS
In a) just divide  by 50 and round to three decimal places.</p>
<p>Answer is 0.3.</p>
<p>In b) divide  by 461 and round to three decimal places.</p>
<p>Answer is 0.301518438177874.</p>
<p>In c) Your answer should be a percentage.  So multiply the decimal
batting average in b) by 100.</p>
<p>Answer is 30.1518438177874.</p>
<p>In d) since batting average is hits/(at bats), hits must be batting
average times at bats,</p>
<p>so multiply 0.277 by at bats and round the
answer to be an integer.</p>
<p>You must round because the batting average
is approximate since it is only calculated to 3 decimal places.</p>
<p>Ans = 41.</p>
</solution>
