      <statement><p>Andrew spent $16 on gasoline last week.</p>
<p>He will spend 25% more on gasoline this week than he did last week.</p>
<p>How much will Andrew spend on gasoline this week? 
<var form="buttons">
<li>
<p>$20</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>$64</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>$24</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>$41</p>
</li>
</var></p>
</statement>
      <solution><p>Solution</p>
<p>25% of 16 is <m>\frac{1}{4}\times 16=4</m>, so he will spend $16+$4=$20.</p>
</solution>
