    <static seed="15" source="Library/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/EquivalentFraction20.pg">
      <statement><p>Find an equivalent fraction to <m>\frac{6}{7}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{6}{7} = \frac{12}{?} }</m></p>
<p>The question mark should be the number <fillin characters="8" name="AnSwEr0001"/>.</p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>14</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>From <m>6</m> to <m>12</m>, we multiplied by <m>12\div6=2</m>.</p>
<p>For a fraction, when we multiply the same number in both the numerator and denominator, the fraction<rsq/>s value doesn<rsq/>t change. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{6}{7}=\frac{6\cdot2}{7\cdot2} = \frac{12}{14} }</m></p>
</solution>
    </static>
