      <statement><p>Neil bought 7 quarts of juice for a party.  One glass holds 8 fluid ounces of juice.</p>
<p>The total number of full glasses that he can fill is <fillin characters="1" name="AnSwEr0001"/>.</p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>28</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>Using dimensional analysis and starting with the number of quarts of juice:</p>
<p><me>7\;\text{quarts} \cdot \frac{32\;\text{ounces}}{1\;\text{quart}} \cdot
\frac{1\;\text{glass}}{8\;\text{ounces}} = 28</me></p>
</solution>
